.Dd April 17, 2026
.Dt MANEATER 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm maneater
.Nd local semantic search with pluggable document sources
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Cm index
.Op Fl -force
.Nm
.Cm init-store
.Nm
.Cm search
.Ar query
.Op Fl -top-k Ar N
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
builds and queries semantic search indexes over pluggable document sources
using vector embeddings.
Man pages are the default built-in corpus; additional corpus types (files,
external commands) allow indexing arbitrary text collections.
See
.Xr maneater.toml 5
for corpus configuration.
.Pp
The following commands are available:
.Bl -tag -width "search"
.It Cm index Op Fl -force
Build or incrementally update the search index.
Unchanged documents (identified by content hash) are skipped; only new or
modified documents are embedded.
Use
.Fl -force
to ignore cached entries and rebuild from scratch.
The index is written to the blob store (see
.Sx BLOB STORAGE )
and reused by subsequent
.Cm search
invocations.
.It Cm init-store
Initialize the blob storage backend.
Sets up the default
.Xr madder 1
content-addressed blob store for sharing indexes across machines.
Creates an XDG user store with the configured store ID
.Pq default: Dq maneater .
Safe to run multiple times; exits immediately if the store already exists.
.It Cm search Ar query Op Fl -top-k Ar N
Search across all configured corpora by natural language query.
Returns ranked results with document keys and cosine similarity scores.
Requires a pre-built index
.Pq Cm maneater index .
The default result count is 10; use
.Fl -top-k
to override.
.El
.Pp
Bare invocation with no command prints usage and exits with status 1.
.Sh SETUP
.Ss Nix (recommended)
Install via the flake:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
nix build github:amarbel-llc/maneater
.Ed
.Pp
The Nix wrapper bundles all dependencies
.Pq mandoc, pandoc, tldr
and sets
.Ev MANEATER_CONFIG
to a bundled configuration with pre-resolved model paths.
.Ss Pre-building the search index
The search index must be built before searching:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
maneater index
.Ed
.Pp
The tldr cache is populated automatically on the first index build
if it does not already exist.
.Ss Without Nix
Manually install the following dependencies:
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
.Xr mandoc 1
.It
.Xr pandoc 1
.It
.Xr tldr 1
.It
llama-cpp (linked at build time via pkg-config)
.El
.Pp
Download a GGUF embedding model and create a configuration file.
See
.Xr maneater.toml 5
for the format.
A minimal example:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
mkdir -p ~/.config/maneater
cat > ~/.config/maneater/maneater.toml <<'EOF'
[models.nomic]
path = "/path/to/nomic-embed-text-v1.5.Q8_0.gguf"
query-prefix = "search_query: "
document-prefix = "search_document: "
EOF
.Ed
.Sh BLOB STORAGE
After building an index,
.Nm
writes the index as a single blob to a content-addressed store.
On subsequent searches, the blob is fetched from the store using the
digest recorded in the manifest.
This allows pre-built indexes to be shared across machines.
.Pp
The blob store is
.Sy required ;
indexing fails if it is not initialized.
.Nm
shells out to
.Xr madder 1
for all blob reads and writes, and the store must be initialized
before first use:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
maneater init-store
.Ed
.Pp
Every search fetches the index blob from the store.
There is no local entries cache.
.Pp
The store ID is configurable via the
.Va [storage]
section in
.Xr maneater.toml 5 .
When no
.Va [storage]
section is present, store ID
.Dq maneater
is used.
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width "MANEATER_CONFIG"
.It Ev MANEATER_CONFIG
Path to a base configuration file loaded as the lowest-priority layer
in the
.Xr maneater.toml 5
hierarchy.
User and project configs overlay on top of it.
Set automatically by the Nix wrapper to a bundled
.Pa maneater.toml
containing model paths and a default manpages corpus.
.It Ev MANPATH
Colon-separated list of directories to search for man pages.
.Nm
delegates to
.Xr manpath 1
to resolve this; if unset,
.Xr manpath 1
falls back to platform defaults.
.Pp
In addition to the system manpath,
.Nm
automatically probes the current working directory for
.Pa man/ ,
.Pa doc/man/ ,
and
.Pa share/man/
subdirectories.
These heuristic paths are prepended to the system manpath so
project-local man pages shadow system pages.
This behavior can be disabled or extended via the
.Va manpath
section in
.Xr maneater.toml 5 .
.It Ev XDG_DATA_HOME
Base directory for persistent index state
.Pq manifests and metadata .
Defaults to
.Pa ~/.local/share .
.It Ev XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for the global configuration file.
Defaults to
.Pa ~/.config .
See
.Xr maneater.toml 5
for the full hierarchy.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "$XDG_DATA_HOME/maneater/index/"
.It Pa $XDG_DATA_HOME/maneater/index/
Persistent index state, organized as:
.Pp
.D1 Pa {corpusName}/{configHash}/manifest.json
.D1 Pa {corpusName}/{configHash}/meta.json
.Pp
The
.Pa configHash
is derived from the model path, document prefix, and corpus parameters.
Changing any of these creates a new state directory.
.Pa manifest.json
records the content-addressed blob digest from the last successful index.
.Pa meta.json
records the full config snapshot for debuggability.
.Pp
Index entries are stored exclusively in the blob store
.Pq see Sx BLOB STORAGE .
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr madder 1 ,
.Xr mandoc 1 ,
.Xr pandoc 1 ,
.Xr tldr 1 ,
.Xr maneater.toml 5
